						               													<description>&amp;quot;Your sleepy little city is on the decline and some new investors want to help change that.  Now you'll compete with other cities, securing the best building projects to gain the most prestige in hopes of become the Greatest Little City.&amp;quot;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;In this game, players will have two actions to perform.  Gaining tiles and placing them within their city.  Gaining a tile involves the Investor's Market, a series of building tile stacks arranged in a rondel.  The active player moves their Investor clockwise to the desired stack, claiming the top tile.  The Active Player pawn then moves clockwise to the next Investor in the rondel.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Between turns at the Investor Market, players can then add these buildings to their cities.  New tiles must be placed adjacent to their City Planner, who then moves onto the newly built tiles.  Each building type scores differently.  Once four piles have been depleted, the game is over.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Greatest Little Cities: Urban Sprawl is the larger box version of Greatest Little Cities, a Mint Tin Game.  The tiles are not only significantly larger from the original but the number of tiles of each type has been rebalanced to add a 5th Player from the original.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;description from the publisher&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
